narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: i would definitely recommend it to a fellow student, it is a great glass

I can summarize this course in three words: Do not bother.I would never recommend this course to a fellow student, and if they truly did not know how to take derivatives (which, by the way, is the point of this course), I would tell them to buy the text book and copy it out verbatim since thats all the teachers do.
If you don't know how to differentiate equations or find very basic integrals, take this class. Otherwise, consider 115.

I would only take it if you need a math requirement for Econ. Otherwise, no. Also, beware that a lot of people in this class have taken AP calc before. So if you have no experience in AP calc, I would definitely not take the class.
If you like math take it.
If you have to take it take it
I would recommend it if they need to take it for a requirement, but not just as another credit.

Shop for every teacher and choose the one with the best English and the most confidence. Anton is fantastic and super smart. He always came to class prepared and smiling. I'm not sure if I can say the same for the other teachers.
